        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 5:34PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 533 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Madeline, or 12 miles northwest of Termo. This thunderstorm was
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Madeline.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
